1012
01:20:28,957 --> 01:20:30,583
But l can't keep it.

1013
01:20:31,709 --> 01:20:35,755
l can't drive that car and work
with people who can't afford to eat.

1014
01:20:36,422 --> 01:20:39,509
Keep the car.
You and Howie will need it.

1015
01:20:41,386 --> 01:20:42,637
Well, Daddy...

1016
01:20:44,013 --> 01:20:46,224
...l'm giving Howie back too.

1017
01:20:48,476 --> 01:20:50,103
l don't love Howie.

1018
01:20:50,895 --> 01:20:52,271
Well, we learn to love.

1019
01:20:52,480 --> 01:20:55,316
l mean, there's marriage
and there's family...

1020
01:20:56,442 --> 01:20:57,902
...and the family business.

1021
01:20:58,194 --> 01:21:00,154
That's what's important.

1022
01:21:00,905 --> 01:21:03,116
l have my own job.

1023
01:21:03,992 --> 01:21:06,744
And l want to get my own apartment.

1024
01:21:07,078 --> 01:21:09,539
But you can keep your job
until you're pregnant.

1025
01:21:11,416 --> 01:21:14,502
l mean, Howie's a fine boy...

1026
01:21:15,086 --> 01:21:17,713
...and l don't think
you need your own apartment.

1027
01:21:19,006 --> 01:21:21,926
-Do you ever hear me?
-Well, l do.

1028
01:21:22,135 --> 01:21:23,678
l don't love Howie.

1029
01:21:26,264 --> 01:21:27,724
l don't love him.

1030
01:21:29,267 --> 01:21:30,351
l love Billy.

1031
01:21:31,144 --> 01:21:32,395
Billy from the roof?

1032
01:22:17,857 --> 01:22:20,860
l took off work because
l thought you wouldn't be here.

1033
01:22:21,110 --> 01:22:22,195
l'm sick.

1034
01:22:23,988 --> 01:22:24,822
What's wrong?

1035
01:22:25,031 --> 01:22:26,741
Just sickness.

1036
01:22:35,541 --> 01:22:37,418
You can't have the Pretenders album.

1037
01:22:38,085 --> 01:22:39,629
-That's mine.
-l bought it.

1038
01:22:39,837 --> 01:22:40,755
You did not!

1039
01:22:43,591 --> 01:22:45,885
You can have all the Billy Joels.

1040
01:22:47,595 --> 01:22:48,763
Except The Stranger.

1041
01:22:50,098 --> 01:22:51,975
l'm taking Thriller...

1042
01:22:52,267 --> 01:22:54,060
...and Mahler's Ninth.

1043
01:22:55,979 --> 01:22:58,022
Kevin is so fond of Mahler.

1044
01:22:59,774 --> 01:23:01,234
l moved in with Jules.

1045
01:23:01,526 --> 01:23:03,152
Oh, how nice.

1046
01:23:03,653 --> 01:23:05,113
Roomies again.

1047
01:23:08,616 --> 01:23:10,660
No Springsteen leaves this house!

1048
01:23:12,495 --> 01:23:14,956
You can have all the Carly Simons.

1049
01:23:15,206 --> 01:23:18,042
You got me those for Valentine's Day.
Remember Valentine's?

1050
01:23:18,751 --> 01:23:21,295
You ran out on this relationship.
Take the consequences.

1051
01:23:21,546 --> 01:23:23,756
l didn't run out on anything.
You ran out.

1052
01:23:24,006 --> 01:23:26,217
-You fucked Kevin!
-You fucked many!

1053
01:23:26,551 --> 01:23:28,177
Nameless, faceless many!

1054
01:23:30,513 --> 01:23:32,557
l feel much better now.

1055
01:23:32,807 --> 01:23:33,975
Thanks.

1056
01:23:44,152 --> 01:23:45,528
You're not taking The Police--

1057
01:23:46,070 --> 01:23:48,614
Anyway, l didn't just fuck Kevin!

1058
01:23:48,865 --> 01:23:52,035
l was confused and angry,
and l care about him deeply.

1059
01:23:52,327 --> 01:23:55,163
Get your clothes,
give me the keys and get out!

1060
01:23:57,290 --> 01:23:58,374
Now!

1061
01:24:02,837 --> 01:24:05,298
l can't believe
this is happening to us.

1062
01:24:13,681 --> 01:24:15,808
Wasted love!

1063
01:24:23,608 --> 01:24:25,985
God, l just wish
l could get it back!

1064
01:24:43,544 --> 01:24:44,378
You did it!

1065
01:24:46,881 --> 01:24:49,967
l think l'll probably
be back doing obits tomorrow.

1066
01:24:50,218 --> 01:24:53,137
