Let me see.

1077
01:25:45,898 --> 01:25:47,150
'' Housing in Maryland''?

1078
01:25:47,441 --> 01:25:49,819
-The other piece.
-''The Meaning of Life.''

1079
01:25:50,069 --> 01:25:53,990
Forrester's waiting. Did the hospital
call? Did my step-monster die?

1080
01:25:54,240 --> 01:25:56,367
-He's waiting.
-l want to meet him.

1081
01:25:56,659 --> 01:25:58,703
Not now, but l'll have him wave up.

1082
01:26:02,415 --> 01:26:05,918
-She's out of control.
-Since the day we met her.

1083
01:26:10,757 --> 01:26:11,591
Who is that?

1084
01:26:11,966 --> 01:26:14,010
Jules' boss and lover.

1085
01:26:19,682 --> 01:26:21,976
lnternational banking
has gotten sexier.

1086
01:26:22,268 --> 01:26:25,938
Speaking of which, not to get ahead
of myself, but l was thinking...

1087
01:26:26,230 --> 01:26:28,191
...maybe we'd get a place together.

1088
01:26:28,441 --> 01:26:29,275
What?

1089
01:26:29,525 --> 01:26:32,361
l know it's fast,
but l also know l love you.

1090
01:26:35,073 --> 01:26:36,783
Sex isn't love.

1091
01:26:43,289 --> 01:26:44,290
What's that mean?

1092
01:26:44,499 --> 01:26:48,502
That means that you were sitting there
with all these feelings...

1093
01:26:48,753 --> 01:26:53,299
...incredible feelings, tied up
in a box with my pictures.

1094
01:26:53,508 --> 01:26:56,177
And l needed to break away from Alec.

1095
01:27:09,315 --> 01:27:11,192
l'm not proud of my behaviour.

1096
01:27:14,112 --> 01:27:16,489
-Hang up.
-Who's that?

1097
01:27:17,031 --> 01:27:18,491
That's not Kevin, is it?

1098
01:27:19,617 --> 01:27:22,078
You're not with Kevin
playing my records?

1099
01:27:22,328 --> 01:27:23,246
Stop it, please.

1100
01:27:23,538 --> 01:27:26,791
-Tell him we're moving in together.
-We are not!

1101
01:27:27,333 --> 01:27:30,503
So the two of you are
moving in together.

1102
01:27:38,136 --> 01:27:41,806
l wish everything could be like
it was, all of us friends.

1103
01:27:42,473 --> 01:27:44,767
l don't want to be friends.

1104
01:27:47,145 --> 01:27:48,521
l didn't mean that.

1105
01:27:48,771 --> 01:27:50,314
l mean, it was an accident.

1106
01:27:51,065 --> 01:27:53,818
l'm beginning to think
there aren't any accidents.

1107
01:27:57,530 --> 01:28:00,283
And l would really like it...

1108
01:28:00,491 --> 01:28:02,535
...if you would just leave.

1109
01:28:03,369 --> 01:28:04,454
Okay?

1110
01:28:12,545 --> 01:28:13,546
Great.

1111
01:28:17,341 --> 01:28:18,968
You were right all along.

1112
01:28:19,218 --> 01:28:21,262
-Love sucks.
-Yep.

1113
01:28:23,640 --> 01:28:26,309
So you gonna get the old job back?

1114
01:28:26,559 --> 01:28:27,894
No way.

1115
01:28:28,853 --> 01:28:32,440
Once l'm back in school,
l'll work part-time for a law firm.

1116
01:28:32,690 --> 01:28:35,610
Did you know there are
as many students in law school...

1117
01:28:35,860 --> 01:28:37,236
...as there are lawyers?

1118
01:28:37,487 --> 01:28:38,821
Sounds familiar.

1119
01:28:46,704 --> 01:28:49,082
l always thought
we'd be friends forever.

1120
01:28:50,708 --> 01:28:55,338
Yeah, well, forever got a lot
shorter suddenly, didn't it?

1121
01:29:01,886 --> 01:29:04,806
Okay, call Mary Dusit at that number.

1122
01:29:05,348 --> 01:29:06,599
Yeah, l'll call.

1123
01:29:14,190 --> 01:29:15,566
l'll call you back.

1124
01:29:23,992 --> 01:29:26,119
l'm sorry to bother you here.

1125
01:29:26,369 --> 01:29:28,663
Did you forget one of your albums?

1126
01:29:28,913 --> 01:29:30,540
lt's Jules.

1127
01:29:31,458 --> 01:29:33,584
After she left for work
this morning...

1128
01:29:33,834 --> 01:29:36,671
...some finance company came
and took everything.

1129
01:29:36,921 --> 01:29:40,174
l couldn't reach her,
so l went over to her office.

1130
01:29:40,466 --> 01:29:42,677
She's been pretending
to go to work...

1131
01:29:42,927 --> 01:29:45,638
...telling me she's having
an affair with her boss.

1132
01:29:45,847 --> 01:29:48,141
He fired her three weeks ago.

1133
01:29:49,309 --> 01:29:51,352
l confronted her,
and she denied everything.

1134
01:29:51,603 --> 01:29:56,315
But then she went crazy. And now
she's locked herself in the apartment.

1135
01:29:59,444 --> 01:30:01,654
Please, l need your help.

1136
01:30:10,455 --> 01:30:12,415
Hi, Jules. Open the door.

1137
01:30:14,458 --> 01:30:16,335
-Open the door.
-She's in there.

1138
01:30:16,544 --> 01:30:18,254
She's got it deadbolted.

1139
01:30:25,094 --> 01:30:27,555
-What's he doing here?
-l called him.

1140
01:30:27,805 --> 01:30:29,849
Did you call all your lovers?

1141
01:30:30,099 --> 01:30:32,727
Will your high-school prom date
be joining us too?

1142
01:30:33,728 --> 01:30:36,647
-What's happening with Jules?
-She's bolted the door.

1143
01:30:37,064 --> 01:30:38,524
The fire escape!

1144
01:30:44,489 --> 01:30:45,490
Open up!

1145
01:30:56,792 --> 01:30:58,336
What are you doing?

1146
01:30:58,878 --> 01:31:01,005
-You'll freeze.
-That's the idea.

1147
01:31:01,255 --> 01:31:02,882
Jules, honey, it's me!

1148
01:31:03,883 --> 01:31:05,677
You're really scaring me now!

1149
01:31:05,885 --> 01:31:08,262
The country's falling apart,
but these bars are perfect.

1150
01:31:08,554 --> 01:31:11,266
-We need a hacksaw.
-Or an experienced thief.

1151
01:31:11,474 --> 01:31:12,559
l'll find Billy.

1152
01:31:12,851 --> 01:31:14,185
l was kidding.

1153
01:31:14,394 --> 01:31:17,563
He's working at the Amoco station.
l'll see what he's got.

1154
01:31:17,855 --> 01:31:20,316
-He's around the corner.
-Billy's working at a gas station?

1155
01:31:20,608 --> 01:31:22,068
He needed the money.

1156
01:31:24,570 --> 01:31:25,488
You little shit!

1157
01:31:32,036 --> 01:31:32,871
Here!

1158
01:31:33,454 --> 01:31:34,372
What's happening?

1159
01:31:34,622 --> 01:31:37,166
-How do you feel now, best friend?
-My notes!

1160
01:31:37,708 --> 01:31:40,002
You won't be needing
your notes anymore.

1161
01:31:40,586 --> 01:31:42,463
Stop it!
You'll kill him!

1162
01:31:42,755 --> 01:31:45,508
This won't solve anything.
Think of your career.

1163
01:31:45,800 --> 01:31:48,636
-Stop it!
-After all l've done for you!

1164
01:31:48,928 --> 01:31:51,139
l've done a lot for you too.
Pull me up.

1165
01:31:51,598 --> 01:31:53,057
What you did for me, you shit...

1166
01:31:53,808 --> 01:31:56,644
...was steal the woman
that l was gonna marry!

1167
01:32:00,106 --> 01:32:01,816
Kirbo, you need any help?

1168
01:32:02,066 --> 01:32:04,777
-Quick!
-Help! Alec, pull him up!

1169
01:32:06,446 --> 01:32:07,822
Looks pretty out of hand.

1170
01:32:08,072 --> 01:32:10,992
Stop it! Do you think this
is helping Jules?

1171
01:32:11,242 --> 01:32:12,243
l love her, man.

1172
01:32:13,202 --> 01:32:14,454
Give me a hand!

1173
01:32:16,873 --> 01:32:18,041
l got it! l got it!

1174
01:32:26,132 --> 01:32:27,842
-You all right?
-Super.

1175
01:32:28,051 --> 01:32:29,135
l'm going upstairs.

1176
01:32:29,552 --> 01:32:32,639
Somebody give me a hand!
Come on!

1177
01:32:32,889 --> 01:32:33,806
Oh, my God!

1178
01:32:34,557 --> 01:32:36,768
Honey, open the door.
lt's so cold.

1179
01:32:37,018 --> 01:32:39,062
Noble how you ran up
to save your lover.

1180
01:32:39,354 --> 01:32:40,897
He's not my lover.

1181
01:32:41,147 --> 01:32:43,107
-Jules, listen--
-Bullshit!

1182
01:32:43,357 --> 01:32:47,028
l've never lied to you since the day
l met you, you cocky shithead!

1183
01:32:48,029 --> 01:32:49,655
-Alec!
-We all love you.

1184
01:32:49,906 --> 01:32:50,990
Help!

1185
01:32:54,827 --> 01:32:56,287
Open this goddamn door!

1186
01:32:58,498 --> 01:33:00,041
-Blowtorch?
-Give it to me.

1187
01:33:00,250 --> 01:33:03,252
-Do not hand that man a blowtorch.
-Put these on.

1188
01:33:06,547 --> 01:33:07,298
Open the door!

1189
01:33:08,132 --> 01:33:11,552
Did you hear me?
Open the door, or l'll bust it down!

1190
01:33:15,473 --> 01:33:17,100
l'm coming through this door!

1191
01:33:17,350 --> 01:33:19,978
You know l'm crazy enough to do it!

1192
01:33:22,063 --> 01:33:22,897
What's happening?

1193
01:33:34,284 --> 01:33:35,451
l'm going in.

1194
01:33:40,540 --> 01:33:41,374
Hi, Billy.

1195
01:33:51,551 --> 01:33:53,761
What's the big deal here?

1196
01:33:53,970 --> 01:33:55,430
You lost a job?

1197
01:33:55,722 --> 01:33:59,142
l've lost 20 of them since graduation.

1198
01:33:59,767 --> 01:34:01,394
Plus a wife and kid.

1199
01:34:02,061 --> 01:34:06,065
ln a new development, a handful
of hair in the shower this morning.

1200
01:34:06,899 --> 01:34:08,359
That's better.

1201
01:34:09,193 --> 01:34:10,194
You know...

1202
01:34:11,028 --> 01:34:14,782
...this smells to me like
a little bit of self-created drama.

1203
01:34:15,199 --> 01:34:18,369
l should know. l've been
starring in a few of my own.

1204
01:34:20,455 --> 01:34:24,208
Do you know what l've been doing
every day since l got fired?

1205
01:34:25,084 --> 01:34:26,002
What?

1206
01:34:26,252 --> 01:34:29,922
l've been sitting in the hospital
with my step-monster.

1207
01:34:32,425 --> 01:34:35,678
We've had the best talks
we've ever had.

1208
01:34:37,138 --> 01:34:41,267
Of course, she's in a coma,
which really pisses me off.

1209
01:34:43,144 --> 01:34:45,354
Because all that time...

1210
01:34:47,648 --> 01:34:49,108
...l just waited...

1211
01:34:49,400 --> 01:34:52,737
...for one word from that woman...

1212
01:34:54,489 --> 01:34:58,701
...about why my father
hates me so much.

1213
01:35:12,673 --> 01:35:14,467
Jules, you know...

1214
01:35:15,968 --> 01:35:17,595
...honey, this isn't real.

1215
01:35:18,054 --> 01:35:19,430
You know what it is?

1216
01:35:19,681 --> 01:35:21,057
lt's St. Elmo's fire.

1217
01:35:21,432 --> 01:35:25,478
The electric flashes of light that
appear in dark skies out of nowhere.

1218
01:35:31,317 --> 01:35:35,238
Sailors would guide entire journeys
by it. But there was no fire.

1219
01:35:35,488 --> 01:35:38,324
There wasn't even a St. Elmo.
They made it up...

1220
01:35:39,284 --> 01:35:43,288
...because they needed it
to keep going when things got tough.

1221
01:35:43,538 --> 01:35:45,915
Just like you're making up
all of this.

1222
01:35:50,336 --> 01:35:52,380
We're all going through this.

1223
01:35:55,007 --> 01:35:57,218
lt's our time on the edge.

1224
01:35:59,554 --> 01:36:02,223
l'm just so tired.

1225
01:36:04,684 --> 01:36:08,688
l never thought l'd be so tired at 22.

1226
01:36:13,067 --> 01:36:16,154
l just don't even know
who to be anymore.

1227
01:36:16,446 --> 01:36:18,072
Join the club.

1228
01:36:22,535 --> 01:36:26,998
No one was buying this together-
woman-of-the-eighties stuff anyway.

1229
01:36:35,256 --> 01:36:39,719
And all this time l was afraid
you'd find out l wasn't fabulous.

1230
01:36:42,055 --> 01:36:43,514
lt's cool.

1231
01:36:44,974 --> 01:36:48,728
All this time l was afraid
you'd find out l was irresponsible.

1232
01:36:54,609 --> 01:36:55,860
They're laughing.

1233
01:36:56,068 --> 01:36:57,945
The hysterical laughter heard...

1234
01:36:58,196 --> 01:37:00,823
...most frequently
from schizophrenic paranoids.

1235
01:37:01,324 --> 01:37:04,661
Set up my drafting table
so we can have coffee on it.

1236
01:37:08,414 --> 01:37:10,375
-Oh, baby.
-l love you.

1237
01:37:16,964 --> 01:37:18,758
And then what happened?

1238
01:37:18,966 --> 01:37:20,051
That was it.

1239
01:37:20,301 --> 01:37:24,347
We came out of the bedroom,
and then l shot her.

1240
01:37:24,889 --> 01:37:26,849
No, you did not.

1241
01:37:27,141 --> 01:37:28,601
You saved her life.

1242
01:37:28,852 --> 01:37:31,145
Oh, let's not be dramatic.

1243
01:37:32,104 --> 01:37:34,565
So when did you get so sane?

1244
01:37:35,107 --> 01:37:38,528
When l realized how insane l'd been
trying to be like Alec.

1245
01:37:39,195 --> 01:37:41,656
l'm not part of this
after-college life.

1246
01:37:41,948 --> 01:37:43,908
Careers. Marriage.

1247
01:37:45,285 --> 01:37:47,328
Felicia and Melody'll be
better off without me.

1248
01:37:47,579 --> 01:37:49,873
